article.description: — Tyler Thomas scored 25 points as Hofstra beat South Florida 82-63 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Hofstra takes down South Florida 82-63
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- — Tyler Thomas scored 25 points as Hofstra beat South Florida 82-63 on Thursday night. Thomas also contributed five rebounds for the Pride (5-2). Darlinstone Dubar added 24 points while shooting 9 for 16, including 4 for 9 from beyond the arc, and he also had 11 rebounds. Jaquan Carlos shot 2 of 4 from the field and 6 for 6 from the line to finish with 11 points. Jayden Reid led the Bulls (2-3) in scoring, finishing with 10 points, five assists and two steals. Selton Miguel added 10 points for South Florida. In addition, Jose Placer finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
